# Code owners — review-gates the most security-sensitive surfaces.
#
# GitHub Actions workflows run with repository secrets in scope (e.g. the
# FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT JSON used by deploy-firebase-rules.yml). A malicious
# edit to a workflow, once merged, could exfiltrate a secret on the next run —
# the paths filter does not protect against that (cage-match #496, Carnot). Make
# any change to a workflow require an explicit owner review.
#
# ENFORCEMENT GATE (Nick): this file is ADVISORY until branch protection on
# `main` enables "Require review from Code Owners". Turn it on at:
#   https://github.com/enspyrco/tech_world/settings/branches
# Until then, treat workflow edits as owner-review-required by discipline.
/.github/workflows/  @nickmeinhold
/.github/CODEOWNERS  @nickmeinhold
